<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000019#     2#          388#">Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-388</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_19.2-388"/><heading><desig>§ 19.2-388.</desig><title>Duties and authority of Exchange</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> It shall be the duty of the Central Criminal Records Exchange to receive, classify and file criminal history record information as defined in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 9.1-101"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 9.1-101">§ 9.1-101<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000009#     1#          101#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and other records required to be reported to it by <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 16.1-299"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 16.1-299">§§ 16.1-299<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000016#     1#          299#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-390"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-390">19.2-390<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#          390#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>. The Exchange is authorized to prepare and furnish to all state and local law-enforcement officials and agencies; to clerks of circuit courts, general district courts, and juvenile and domestic relations district courts; and to corrections and penal officials, forms which shall be used for the making of such reports.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Juvenile records received pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 16.1-299"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 16.1-299">§ 16.1-299<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000016#     1#          299#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> shall be maintained separately from adult records.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 19.1-19.2; 1966, c. 669; 1968, c. 537; 1970, c. 118; 1975, c. 495; 1976, c. 771; 1982, c. 33; <citation normalizedCite="1993 VA CH 468"><content><span normalizedCite="1993 Va. Ch. 468">1993, cc. 468<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1993#000468#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1993 VA CH 926"><content><span normalizedCite="1993 Va. Ch. 926">926<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1993#000926#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1996 VA CH 755"><content><span normalizedCite="1996 Va. Ch. 755">1996, cc. 755<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1996#000755#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1996 VA CH 914"><content><span normalizedCite="1996 Va. Ch. 914">914<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1996#000914#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativ